           <history>
               <origin>
                   <origDate notBefore="1700" to="1875" evidence="lettering"/>
               </origin>
               <provenance>
                   No information is available on the provenance and early history of the manuscript, except for the presence of <ref target="#a2">a summary of the book contents</ref>
                   written in Arabic on the back board, which might suggest that the manuscript was produced or circulated at some time in an Arabic-speaking country.
                   The names of the original owners have been erased and replaced with those of <persName ref="PRS14037Zamaryam"/> and
                   <persName ref="PRS14039Enzira"/> (the two names might also possibly refer to one single person).
                   The manuscript was then acquired by <persName ref="PRS9622Ullendor" role="owner"/>.
                  </provenance>
           </history>

